  "prompt": "I feel sad when?",
  "response": "Feeling sad is a natural and human emotion that can be triggered by various situations or circumstances. Here are some common reasons why you might feel sad:\n\n1. **Loss or Grief**  \n   - Losing a loved one, a pet, or something meaningful can bring deep sadness.\n\n2. **Disappointment**  \n   - Not achieving a goal, failing at something, or unmet expectations can lead to sadness.\n\n3. **Loneliness**  \n   - Feeling isolated, disconnected, or unsupported can make you feel down.\n\n4. **Stress or Overwhelm**  \n   - Facing challenges, pressure, or uncertainty can weigh heavily on your emotions.\n\n5. **Conflict**  \n   - Arguments, misunderstandings, or strained relationships can cause sadness.\n\n6. **Reflecting on the Past**  \n   - Nostalgia or regrets about past events might bring feelings of sadness.\n\n7. **Unfulfilled Needs**  \n   - When your emotional, physical, or social needs aren\u2019t met, it can lead to sadness.\n\n8. **Witnessing Suffering**  \n   - Seeing others in pain or experiencing hardship can make you feel sad.\n\n9. **Changes or Transitions**  \n   - Major life changes, like moving, ending a relationship, or starting something new, can trigger sadness.\n\n10. **Self-Criticism**  \n    - Being hard on yourself or feeling inadequate can contribute to sadness.\n\nIt\u2019s important to acknowledge your feelings and give yourself permission to feel sad. If sadness persists or feels overwhelming, reaching out to someone you trust or seeking professional help can be a helpful step. You\u2019re not alone, and it\u2019s okay to ask for support. \u2764\ufe0f",
